text: {| |} Seminole (YT‑805) is a United States Navy . ==Construction== The contract for Seminole was awarded 25 March 2008. She was laid down by J.M. Martinac Shipbuilding Corp., Tacoma, Washington and launched 6 November 2010. ==Operational history== Seminole was delivered to the Navy 8 April 2011 at Yokosuka by the US-flagged heavy-lift ship BBC Houston. Seminole is assigned to Commander Fleet Activities Yokosuka. ==References== * * Category:Valiant- class tugboats Category:Ships built in Tacoma, Washington Category:2010 ships
